	7. Write a program that asks a user for the name of an item and its price and stores this information in 2 separate variables.
		○ The item name must be a String
		○ The price must be a Float
		○ Calculate a 10% discount (Price multiplied by 0.9) and print: "The new price for [item] is [discounted price]", where ‘[item]’ and ‘[discounted price]’ is where you reference your variables.
	
	Answer:
  item = input("name an item")
  price = float(input("how much does it cost"))
	discount = price * 0.9
  print("the new price is", discount)
	
	
